# Sourced by the X session before the WM starts; everything in the
# session inherits these.

# Qt apps outside KDE (quickshell's tray menus, pavucontrol-qt, ...) have
# no platform theme under awesome and default to light Fusion. The
# xdgdesktopportal theme asks the portal for the color scheme — our GTK
# portal backend answers from the GSettings that system-theme-apply
# writes, so Qt follows the shell's dark/light mode.
export QT_QPA_PLATFORMTHEME=xdgdesktopportal
